traceability.evidence:
Implementation inspects version times via npm view and calculates age only for the “latest” version for each package, not for all versions newer than the current:
• fetch-version-times.js returns a map of all version→date but print-outdated.js only does: const latestTime = versionTimes[info.latest]; age = calculateAgeInDays(latestTime);
• No code enumerates every version > current or prints their individual ages. • No optimization to only fetch newer versions is implemented (npm view always returns all). • Tests cover fetchVersionTimes parsing/retries and that the CLI prints an Age column for the latest version, but there are no tests for multiple-version ages or smart fetching.
